  "text": "atients with hypertension and left ventricular hypertrophy (LVH) have a 10-fold greater likelihood of developing heart failure than those with hypertension and a normal LV mass. [CITATION_1] LVH is a structural adaptive mechanism to increased workload, whereas LV failure is the end stage of hypertensive heart disease, resulting from an inability of the heart to adapt to a chronically increased pressure overload. [CITATION_2] The mechanisms whereby hypertension causes cardiac failure are, however, poorly understood.",
